{"title_page": "Blue Carrier 1", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2016}}\n{|{{Infobox ship begin |display title=ital}}\n{{Infobox ship image\n| Ship image               = Anglia seaways.jpg\n| Ship caption             = ''Anglia Seaways'' in [[Heysham]]\n}}\n{{Infobox ship career\n| Hide header              =\n| Ship name                =* ''Maersk Anglia'' (2000\u20132010)\n*''Anglia Seaways'' (2010\u20132019)\n*''Blue Carrier 1'' (2019\u2013present)<ref name=\"equasis\">{{csr|register=E|id=9186649|shipname=Blue Carrier 1|accessdate=18 August 2019}}</ref>\n| Ship owner               = * [[Norfolkline]] (2000\u20132010)\n* [[DFDS]] (2011\u20132019)\n* [[Blue Star Ferries]] (2019\u2013present)<ref name=\"equasis\" />\n| Ship operator            =* Norfolkline (2000-2010)\n* DFDS Seaways (2010-2011)\n* Seatruck Ferries (2011-2012)\n* DFDS Seaways (2012)\n* Seatruck Ferries\n* DFDS Seaways (2014)\n* Blue Star Ferries (2019\u2013present)\n| Ship registry            = * {{flag|Netherlands}} (2010-2011)\n* {{flag|Denmark}} (DIS) (2011\u20132019)\n* {{flag|Greece}} (2019\u2013present)\n| Ship route               = <!-- Immingham - Rotterdam -->\n| Ship ordered             =\n| Ship builder             = [[COMEC (company)|Guangzhou Shipyard International]], [[China]]<ref name=\"seaweb\">{{csr|register=SEAWEB|id=9186649|shipname=Blue Carrier 1|accessdate=18 August 2019}}</ref>\n| Ship original cost       =\n| Ship yard number         = 7130011<ref name=\"seaweb\" />\n| Ship laid down           = 11 June 1999<ref name=\"seaweb\" />\n| Ship launched            = \n| Ship completed           = May 2000<ref name=\"seaweb\" />\n| Ship christened          =\n| Ship acquired            = \n| Ship maiden voyage       = 8 July 2000\n| Ship in service          = \n| Ship out of service      =\n| Ship identification      = * {{IMO Number|9186649}}\n* {{MMSI|241671000}}\n* [[Maritime call sign|Call sign]]: SVCU5\n| Ship fate                =\n| Ship status              = In service\n| Ship notes               = \n}}\n{{Infobox ship characteristics\n| Hide header              =\n| Header caption           = <ref name=\"equasis\" /><ref name=\"seaweb\" />\n| Ship class               = \n| Ship tonnage             = * {{GT|13,073}}\n* {{NetT|4,650}}\n| Ship displacement        = 11,400{{nbsp}}tons\n| Ship length              = {{convert|142.5|m|ftin|abbr=on}}\n| Ship beam                = {{convert|23.2|m|ftin|abbr=on}}\n| Ship height              = {{convert|38.4|m|ftin|abbr=on}} (keel to mast)\n| Ship draft               = {{convert|5.4|m|ftin|abbr=on}}\n| Ship depth               = {{convert|13.15|m|ftin|abbr=on}}\n| Ship decks               = 3\n| Ship deck clearance      =\n| Ship ramps               =\n| Ship power               = 2{{nbsp}}&times;{{nbsp}}Sulzer 8ZAL40S (2{{nbsp}}&times;{{nbsp}}5,370{{nbsp}}kW)\n| Ship propulsion          = Two shafts; [[controllable pitch propeller]]s\n| Ship speed               = {{convert|18.5|kn}}\n| Ship capacity            =*1,680 lane metres\n*121 trailers\n*12 Passengers\n| Ship crew             =\n| Ship notes               =\n}}\n|}\n\n'''MS ''Blue Carrier 1''''' is a [[ro-ro ferry]] built in 2000 for Norfolkline BV and now operates in the [[Aegean Sea]] for [[Blue Star Ferries]].\n\n==History==\n===Norfolk Line===\n[[File:Maersk Anglia.jpg|thumb|left|''Maersk Anglia'' in [[Great Yarmouth]] in 2006]]\nThe vessel was built at the Guangzhou Wenchong shipyard in China for [[Norfolkline|Norfolk Line]], originally being named [[MS Maersk Anglia|''Maersk Anglia'']]. The vessel first operated on the [[Scheveningen]] to [[Felixstowe]] route until 2006 when it was moved onto the [[Vlaardingen]] to Felixstowe route. In 2009 the vessel was moved to the Irish Sea and deployed on the Heysham to Dublin route.\n\n===DFDS Seaways===\nIn July 2010 the vessel was sold to DFDS Seaways and renamed ''Anglia Seaways'' - but remained on the Heysham to Dublin route.\n\nIn February 2011 the vessel was chartered to Seatruck Ferries and was deployed on the Heysham to Dublin route until 15 January 2012.\n\nThen she was transferred over to the Immingham-Rotterdam route which she remained on until 30 April when the vessel was moved onto the Rosyth-Zeebrugge route.\n\nIn late May 2012 she was again chartered to [[Seatruck Ferries]] and operated on the Heysham-Warrenpoint route. In April 2014 the repainted ship operates for DFDS between Kiel and [[Kronstadt]].\n\n===Attica Group===\nFollowing a May 2019 agreement between DFDS and [[Attica Group]], the ship was sold to the latter for 12m euros<ref>https://www.attica-group.com/attachments/article/2501/AGREEMENT_FOR_THE_ACQUISITION_OF_A_RO-RO_CARGO_VESSEL.pdf</ref>. As of July 2019, she has been renamed Blue Carrier 1 and bears the Greek flag. It is expected to augment the ro-ro freight capacity of Attica Group in its Aegean sea routes.<ref>https://www.naftemporiki.gr/story/1494284/new-ferry-boat-acquired-by-attica-group-renamed-blue-carrier-1</ref>\n\n==Description==\n''Anglia Seaways'' is a roll on-roll off freight ferry 142.5 metres in length capable of carrying 121 trailers or 1,680 [[lane metres]]. It is powered by two Sulzer diesel engines which allow the vessel to reach a speed of {{convert|18|kn|mph}}.<ref>{{cite web|title=M/S MAERSK ANGLIA (2000)|url=http://www.faktaomfartyg.se/maersk_anglia_2000.htm|publisher=Fakta om Fartyg|accessdate=23 May 2012}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{commons category-inline|IMO 9186649}}\n* [http://www.dfdsgroup.com/fleet/ro%20ro/angliaseaways/ dfdsgroup.com]\n* [https://archive.is/20130628014616/http://midshipphotos.weebly.com/mv-anglia-seaways.html MV Anglia Seaways photos]\n\n{{Seatruck Ships}}\n\n[[Category:Ships of Seatruck Ferries]]\n[[Category:2000 ships]]\n[[Category:Ships built in China]]\n[[Category:Merchant ships of Denmark]]\n\n{{Ferry-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2016}}\n{|{{Infobox ship begin |display title=ital}}\n{{Infobox ship image\n|