sissippi|Topton]]\n* [[Whynot, Mississippi|Whynot]]\n* [[Zero, Mississippi|Zero]]\n\n==Notable people==\n* [[Samuel Dale]] (1772\u20131841), American frontiersman, known as the \"Daniel Boone of Alabama\" and a veteran of the [[Creek War]] of 1813-14.  In 1836, Dale was elected as Lauderdale County's first representative in the Mississippi state legislature.<ref>{{cite web | last = Lewis | first = Herbert J. \"Jim\" | title = Samuel Dale | publisher = Encyclopedia of Alabama | date = July 25, 2012 | url = http://www.encyclopediaofalabama.org/article/h-2460}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Mississippi}}\n* [[National Register of Historic Places listings in Lauderdale County, Mississippi]]\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n==External links==\n* [http://lauderdalecounty.org/ Lauderdale County, MS]\n* [http://www.visitmeridian.com/ Meridian/Lauderdale County Tourism Bureau]\n* [http://www.mississippicourthouses.com/lauderdale/ Laurerdale County Courthouse Pictures]\n\n{{Geographic Location\n|Centre    = Lauderdale County, Mississippi\n|North     = [[Kemper County, Mississippi|Kemper County]]\n|Northeast = \n|East      = [[Sumter County, Alabama]]\n|Southeast = [[Choctaw County, Alabama]]\n|South     = [[Clarke County, Mississippi|Clarke County]]\n|Southwest = \n|West      = [[Newton County, Mississippi|Newton County]]\n|Northwest = \n}}\n\n{{Lauderdale County, Mississippi}}\n{{Mississippi}}\n\n{{coord|32.40|-88.66|display=title|type:adm2nd_region:US-MS_source:UScensus1990}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Lauderdale County, Mississippi| ]]\n[[Category:Mississippi counties]]\n[[Category:County in Meridian micropolitan area]]\n[[Category:1833 establishments in Mississippi]]\n[[Category:Populated places established in 1833]]\n", "name_user": "Whoisjohngalt", "label": "safe", "comment": "Cleaned up usingAutoEd", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lauderdale_County,_Mississippi"}
